<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-02-08T12:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-02-08T12:45:00-05:00" n="773" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d773">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">717.2114/85: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eberhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-08T12:00:00-05:45">February 8,
                                        1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:55
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>43. Department’s 23, February 2, 8 p.m. In compliance with the
                                Department’s instructions I have again discussed the matter with the
                                    <pb facs="1071" n="935" xml:id="pg_935"/> President and he told
                                me that he would urge approval of the treaty during the present
                                session of Congress.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Eberhardt</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>